#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION THE SIGIL OF ENAERAI


Knights receive the sigil of Enaerai, a mark depicting the Eye of
Enaerai symbol, when they first take the oath of Knighthood upon
themselves.  For some, particularly those Knights who would find
themselves within the division of the Mett, the sigil may not be
visible, but exists nonetheless.

The sigil grants Knights a small measure of protection from holy and
negative powers, as well as a slight increase of combat abilities.
It also assists in communications among the Knight Order.  Knights
may speak to each other in the following manner:

 knighttell <message>  or kt <message>

Those who wear the sigil can also address a note to all Knights by 
doing the follwing:


 note to Knights

