#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS nine
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION USE OF THE SCALE OF ORLIN

The Knight Lord is given charge to care for and instruct Knights in the use
of the Scale of Orlin.  The Scale of Orlin is a complex instrument, only
understood by those dedicated to Enaerai and in the knight order.  It
measures the balance between good and evil, between law and chaos, and
between the strength of the houses.  It gives priority to the measure in
that order, as should the Knights.  The scale is used in the following
manner:

consult scale 


#END_EEXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS eight
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION NAMING A RENEGADE KNIGHT

Only the Knight Lord may declare a Knight to be renegade and oathbreaker. 
Normally, Knights accused of oathbreaking are given warning and an
opportunity to defend themselves (in a simple court, as directed by the
Lord).  The naming of renegade is a last resort, to declare to the Knight
that their mortal life, which is sworn to Enaerai, is forfeit.  When a
Knight is judged to be renegade, and is present in the realm, the Knight
Lord uses the oathstone in the following manner: 

renegade <name>


#END_EEXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS seven
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION DEMOTING AN OFFICER OF THE KNIGHTS

For whatever reason, if a leader among the Knights is to be demoted or
returned to standard Knight status, the administrator, before the oath
stone, asks the Knight whether they accept the removal of office.  The
Knight must respond "I accept" (and should be so informed), and then the
administrator binds the act through use of the oath stone, as follows:

oath knight <name> 


#END_EEXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS six
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION ADMINISTERING THE LORD OATH

At least two Knight Captains must agree on the candidate for the Knight
Lord position, and the prospective Knight Lord given the oath by another
Captain, for the oath ceremony and granting of rank to be considered 
valid before Enaerai.

As with the other oath ceremonies, the candidate stands in the gold ring,
before a Knight Captain.  The candidate is formally charged with directing
the Knighthood and taking responsibility for the balance of Avendar before
Enaerai.  The Captain then questions: "Will you accept this charge?" 
The candidate must respond "I will" (and should be informed beforehand that
those are the necessary words to be uttered, for the oath stone to bind the
ceremony).

This done, the administrator of the oath uses the oath stone in the
following manner:

oath lord <name>

#END_EEXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS five
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION ADMINISTERING THE CAPTAIN OATH

Traditionally, the candidate for the captaincy stands in the gold ring
before the Knight Lord (or another Captain, in the Lord's absence).  The
candidate is formally charged with directing and upholding the work of the
division they are to direct.  The administrator then questions: "Will you
pledge to faithfully serve Enaerai and the balance as Knight Captain?"  The
candidate must respond "I will" (and should be informed beforehand that
those are the requisite ceremonial words that must be uttered, for the oath
stone to bind the ceremony).  

This done, the administrator of the oath uses the oath stone in the
following manner: 

oath captain <name> 


#END_EEXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS four
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION ADMINISTERING THE KNIGHT OATH

The worthy applicant traditionally stands in the gold ring before the Knight
Lord (or Captain, in the Lord's absence).  The applicant is questioned
regarding their desire to take the oath, whether it is done of their own
volition, and whether they understand the consequenses of breaking the oath.


If the applicant gives satisfactory answers, the adminstrator of the oath
questions: "Will you take the oath upon yourself now?"  The applicant must
respond "I will" (and should be informed beforehand that those are the
proper ceremonial words, without which the oath stone will not bind the
oath).  

This done, the administrator of the oath uses the oath stone in the
following manner: 

oath knight <name>


#END_EEXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS three
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION THE KNIGHT GUARD

In the temple of Enaerai, a Knight stands guard at the doors of the
compound.  He will permit only Knights to pass the doors, and those the
Knights wish to invite within the compound.  If Knights wish to invite
someone into the compound, they may say the following: 

escort <name>

The guard will alert all Knights when others attempt to force their way into
the compound, and will also attack renegades of the Knighthood on sight.  

#END_EEXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS two
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION THE PRIEST OF ENAERAI

In the temple of Enaerai in Earendam, a priest tends the altar.  He will
also occasionally grant his blessings and spells upon Knights who are in the
temple.  

Like most temple priests, he can heal for a price, but he'll also grant
benedictions and heal wounds for Knights, of his own accord, and when his
duties permit.  

The priest will also hold items for the Knights, though he will drop
artifacts of great power (such as the Stones of Power) as such items have
the potential to influence the balance and should not be in the temple.  

If a Knight wishes to request the last item given to the priest, the Knight
may do the following: 

request

Finally, when a Knight prays in the presence of the priest in the temple,
the Knight will be able to discern whether Enaerai is near to the realm of
mortals and the prayer is heard, or whether she is distant.  If she is
distant, the priest will take note of the prayer, and Enaerai will receive
the prayer at a later time, when she once more draws near to the mortal
realm.  

#END_EEXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#BEGIN_EXTRA_DESCRIPTION
#KEYWORDS one
#EXTRA_DESCRIPTION THE CODE OF THE KNIGHTS OF ENAERAI

The Knights of Enaerai seek to uphold the balance in Avendar.  By persuasion
or by force, and acting as a unified military body, the Knights are ever
vigilant that no extreme influence disrupts the equilibrium and natural
balance as created when the three great powers first brought Avendar into
being.  

The Knights revere Enaerai, who is held as their guiding deity of balance,
though no active worship is required throughout the Order.  They also
observe Mettenday, the first calendar day of every month on the standard
Avendarian calendar, as a day of rest, recuperation, and assembly.  No
efforts to actively enforce balance are made by the Knights on Mettenday. 
The Knights are based in the city of Earendam, in a compound adjunct to the
Temple of Enaerai.  

REQUIREMENTS OF KNIGHTHOOD

Adventurers who are neutral in both alignment and ethos may become Knights
of Enaerai.  However, scholars who practice the greater spells of spirit or
void, and templars of those spheres, may not seek entrance to the
Knighthood.  To join the Knights of Enaerai, seek out members of the order
and petition them for entrance.  Knights may be recognized by the symbol of
Enaerai--the eye within a triangle.  

THE OFFICES OF KNIGHTHOOD

The organization of the Knighthood is straightforward, run with the
efficiency and manner one would expect of a military order.  Knights heed
the directions of their superiors without question, sacrificing life and
even soul to the cause.  

The Knight Lord leads the Knights.  He or she is the highest officer and
supreme commander of the Knights, maintaining the order of the knighthood
and directing them in actions to right the balance.  

There are up to three captains of the Knights, who vote for the new Lord
should the office be absent.  Each is also given the leadership of the Mett,
Idris, or Ilthar divisions of the Knights.  

The Captain of Mett is charged with subterfuge, spying, scouting, and
providing necessary reconnaissance, as well as leading the rogue component
and other miscellaneous forces of the Knight body.  

The Captain of Idris pools and compiles knowledge regarding adventurers in
the land and their effects on the balance, and the balance between houses,
as well as leading the magical or scholarly forces of the Knight body.  

The Captain of Ilthar is charged with being the second, under the Knight
Lord, to direct in battle, to administer punishment of final death to
renegade Knights who have broaken their oaths of Knighthood, and to lead the
warrior forces of the Knight body.  
